A vintage 1950s-style illustration showing a crowded corporate boardroom where executives in mid-century suits huddle around a single small, glowing computer terminal, their faces showing exaggerated expressions of curiosity, confusion, and nervous anticipation. The room has wood-paneled walls with retro atomic-age decorative elements. Through a large window, other office workers peer in enviously. The color palette features muted teals, warm oranges, and cream tones typical of vintage advertising art. The executives' body language suggests they're both fascinated and completely bewildered by the technology before them, some leaning in too close, others standing back skeptically with crossed arms.
